<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>CSS Background Image</title>
<style>
body {
height: 1500px; /* Added to enable scrolling */
margin: 0;
font-family: Arial, sans-serif;

background-image: url("https://images.pexels.com/photos/129731/pexels-photo-
129731.jpeg");

background-repeat: repeat-x; /* Tile horizontally */
background-position: center 50%; /* Halfway down the page */
background-attachment: fixed; /* Fixed during scrolling */
}
h1 {
text-align: center;
padding-top: 20px;
}
p {
margin: 40px;
font-size: 18px;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1>CSS Background Image Demonstration</h1>

<p>
Scroll the page to observe that the background image remains fixed in position,
tiles horizontally, and appears halfway down the page.
</p>
<p>
This example demonstrates the use of background-image, background-repeat,
background-position, and background-attachment properties in CSS.
</p>
</body>
</html>
